commentTextItems.html: good length delivery outside the off stump, Bradshaw drives it straight to cover fielder, and that will be end of the match

commentPostTextItems.html: New Zealand wins this match by 91 runs and leads the 5-ODI series 4-0. That will be end of our coverage, Please join with us for the 5th and final ODI between this two teams 3rd March 2006. Till then bye from us.

milestones.description: Nathan Astle and Lou Vincent's 156-run partnership is NZ's highest for the 2nd wicket in ODIs, breaking the record of 148 between Fleming and Marshall
Fleming has broken the record for playing the most ODIs (251) for NZ, going past Chris Harris

stories.title: Kiwis losing interest in Windies
stories.subTitle: West Indies in New Zealand 2005-06
stories.summary: New Zealanders are rapidly losing respect for and interest in the sorry West Indies team

stories.title: New Zealand surge to another big win
stories.subTitle: New Zealand v West Indies, 4th ODI, Napier
stories.summary: A total of 324 - thanks to Lou Vincent's confidence-coated 102 and fifties from Nathan Astle and Stephen Fleming - proved more than enough for New Zealand to power to a 91 -run win at McLean Park
